# Runtime options for the interactive development container on an execution host.
#
# An execution host runs a single-file image you built and exported elsewhere with
# "rr.sh --export-sif", then launched here with "rr.sh --run-sif" -- most often a
# compute cluster that cannot build images itself.
#
# This file belongs to your project. Riprap creates it once and never updates it,
# so options you enable here survive `copier update`. It is ordinary project
# content: commit it to share one environment with your team, or leave it
# untracked to configure a single machine.
#
# These options are separate from the build host's ".riprap/user/podman/run-options"
# because runtime options are runtime-specific: an option that grants one runtime
# access to the host's GPUs is not valid for the other.
#
# Format
#   One runtime argument per line. Blank lines, and lines whose first non-blank
#   character is "#", are ignored. An option that carries a value must occupy a
#   single line in "--name=value" form, with no space before the value:
#
#       --nv                     correct
#       --bind /scratch:/scratch correct
#       --bind /scratch /scratch rejected: this is two arguments on one line
#
#   Launching fails with the offending line when a line is not a single argument
#   beginning with "-". Riprap passes every option through to Apptainer verbatim
#   and attaches no meaning to any of them, so consult the `apptainer shell`
#   documentation for what an option does.
#
#   These options are applied in addition to the workspace bind, the credential
#   binds, the containment and clean-environment options, and the working
#   directory, which are always present.
#
# Expose the host's NVIDIA GPUs to the container
#   Uncomment the line below to run CUDA software inside the development container
#   on a host with the NVIDIA driver installed. Apptainer's "--nv" flag binds the
#   host driver libraries and devices into the container.
#
# --nv
